# Repo skill library

Canonical skills live in `.agents/skills`. `pnpm run skills:link` repairs the
tracked agent-facing symlinks so every tool resolves back to that same repo
payload. To copy from `~/.agents/skills` into `.agents/skills` (then commit as
you like), run `pnpm run skills:vendor` (requires `rsync` and a real directory at
`.agents/skills`, not a symlink).

- `.cursor/skills` → `../.agents/skills`
- `.codex/skills` → `../.agents/skills`
- `.agent/skills` → `../.agents/skills`
- `.claude/skills` → `../.agents/skills`
- `.github/skills` → `../.agents/skills`

When work matches packaged guidance, read the relevant `SKILL.md` under
`.agents/skills/<skill-id>/` (or via the symlinks above) instead of guessing.
